questions.text: "I find it difficult to relax when I see something that needs improvement or fixing."
"I feel strongly that fairness and justice should be upheld as a matter of principle."
"I tend to feel a moral obligation to meet higher standards than I expect from others."
"I feel an inner pressure to improve things and hold myself to a higher standard, even when no one is watching."
"I often neglect my own needs because I feel fulfilled when Iâ€™m making others feel loved and supported."
"I tend to feel hurt if my efforts to help others are not acknowledged."
"I instinctively notice when someone needs support and feel drawn to help them."
"I feel a strong emotional need to be valued by the people I care about."
"I feel driven to succeed and fear being seen as incapable, unremarkable, or a failure."
